ðŸ”µ Structure of FormArray

1.FormArray contains multiple AbstractControls.

2.Each item inside FormArray can be:

FormControl

FormGroup

Another FormArray

3.This makes it flexible and powerful.

ðŸ”µ Key Characteristics

1.Controls are accessed using index.

2.Supports validation.

3.Supports dynamic add/remove.

4.Can be nested inside FormGroup.

5.Works with valueChanges and statusChanges.

ðŸ”µ Important Methods of FormArray

1.push() â†’ Add new control

2.removeAt(index) â†’ Remove specific control

3.clear() â†’ Remove all controls

4.at(index) â†’ Get control by index

5.length â†’ Get total number of controls

ðŸ”µ FormArray Validation Concept

1.Validation can be applied to:

Individual controls

Entire FormArray

2.Useful for enforcing:

Minimum items

Maximum items

Required fields inside array

ðŸ”µ Real-World Importance

1.FormArray is essential for enterprise-level dynamic forms.

2.It helps manage unpredictable user input structures.

3.It is commonly used in admin dashboards and data-entry systems.

